<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for encrypting and decrypting the PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to add encryption and decryption in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<Paragraph>
This sample demonstrates the following features:
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Encrypt a PowerPoint presentation using agile encryption, like Office 2010 and 2013.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Decrypt the encrypted PowerPoint presentation using both agile and standard (Office 2007) encryption.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Mark a PowerPoint presentation as 'Final' or 'Read-only'.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note:</Bold> The encrypted presentation can only be read by Office 2007 SP2 compatibility pack or later Office versions.</Paragraph>
